JOHNS: I forgot to mention,

1036
01:41:52,529 --> 01:41:54,197
there's no weapons for you.

1037
01:42:00,995 --> 01:42:02,914
You think you can ride
one of these things?

1038
01:42:03,540 --> 01:42:05,542
I'll ride it like I stole it.

1039
01:42:20,181 --> 01:42:21,725
I'll take flank.

1040
01:42:32,694 --> 01:42:34,904
If Riddick comes back here without us,

1041
01:42:34,946 --> 01:42:38,074
you go ahead,
you kill him on general principle.

1042
01:42:38,324 --> 01:42:41,369
Is that before or after
I'm supposed to fuck him?

1043
01:43:13,985 --> 01:43:15,278
(SNARLING)

1044
01:44:09,457 --> 01:44:10,709
(GRUNTS)

1045
01:44:21,344 --> 01:44:23,013
(GROANING)

1046
01:44:39,487 --> 01:44:40,905
(CREATURES SCREECHING)

1047
01:45:08,725 --> 01:45:10,060
(PERSON WHISTLES)

1048
01:45:13,563 --> 01:45:16,524
You asshole motherfucker!
Just sittin' there watchin'!

1049
01:45:16,566 --> 01:45:20,278
Would have covered you,
but you said, "No weapons."

1050
01:45:26,659 --> 01:45:29,537
How bad you want those nodes, Johns?

1051
01:46:05,323 --> 01:46:08,618
I don't suppose you took the
time to do this for him, huh?

1052
01:46:10,787 --> 01:46:13,540
This may come as a shock to you, Johns,

1053
01:46:14,958 --> 01:46:16,960
but I didn't ghost your son.

1054
01:46:19,087 --> 01:46:21,631
He seemed set on killin' himself.

1055
01:46:25,010 --> 01:46:26,886
What the fuck does that mean?

1056
01:46:27,637 --> 01:46:29,097
Morphine.

1057
01:46:30,640 --> 01:46:32,267
Your son liked his morphine.

1058
01:46:33,560 --> 01:46:35,478
Liked it twice a day.

1059
01:46:36,354 --> 01:46:38,857
Didn't know your son was a junkie?

1060
01:46:42,360 --> 01:46:44,362
Johns was like most Mercs.

1061
01:46:45,071 --> 01:46:48,366
They look all stand-up and do-right

1062
01:46:49,075 --> 01:46:51,911
until you cut them open
and you find something missing.

1063
01:46:52,912 --> 01:46:54,831
In his case, a spine.

1064
01:46:56,916 --> 01:47:00,253
I don't have to listen to this shit!
That's not the man I knew.

1065
01:47:00,337 --> 01:47:02,672
Then you didn't know your son.

1066
01:47:07,802 --> 01:47:09,846
He wanted to kill a kid.

1067
01:47:11,431 --> 01:47:13,266
To save his own skin.

1068
01:47:13,850 --> 01:47:15,977
I had a problem with that.

1069
01:47:17,437 --> 01:47:19,397
You expect me to believe

1070
01:47:19,939 --> 01:47:22,984
my son was gonna kill a child
to save his own life?

1071
01:47:25,236 --> 01:47:29,074
RIDDICK: Morphine makes
the brain soft. Heart weak.

1072
01:47:32,619 --> 01:47:34,662
JOHNS: I don't fuckin' buy it!

1073
01:47:35,038 --> 01:47:37,248
I just can't believe that
my son's the bad guy

1074
01:47:37,332 --> 01:47:40,418
in this fuckin' demented
fairy tale of yours.

1075
01:47:43,254 --> 01:47:45,215
No reason to lie now.

1076
01:47:48,093 --> 01:47:49,260
Johns.

1077
01:47:52,639 --> 01:47:54,140
Either one of us.

1078
01:48:01,898 --> 01:48:03,942
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1079
01:48:08,988 --> 01:48:10,240
(YELLS)

1080
01:48:13,076 --> 01:48:14,744
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1081
01:48:23,294 --> 01:48:25,755
Thanks for startin'
the killing spree for me, Riddick.

1082
01:48:25,839 --> 01:48:27,757
But I'll take it from here.

1083
01:48:27,799 --> 01:48:29,134
(GRUNTING)

1084
01:48:32,595 --> 01:48:34,097
(GROANING)

1085
01:48:41,187 --> 01:48:42,522
(GRUNTING)

1086
01:48:46,901 --> 01:48:47,902
(GRUNTS)

1087
01:48:56,494 --> 01:48:57,704
(GRUNTS)

1088
01:48:58,705 --> 01:49:00,457
- (GRUNTS)
- (GROANING)

1089
01:49:20,352 --> 01:49:21,644
Jamoke.

1090
01:49:26,649 --> 01:49:29,569
So that blade you buried
was meant for me?

1091
01:49:31,112 --> 01:49:33,615
Anyone who deserved it, really.

1092
01:49:36,993 --> 01:49:38,328
We've got a problem, Riddick,

1093
01:49:40,288 --> 01:49:42,832
because I've got two nodes here.

1094
01:49:42,916 --> 01:49:44,793
We've got one hog.

1095
01:49:44,959 --> 01:49:49,005
And I sure as shit
am not ridin' bitch with you again.

1096
01:49:51,341 --> 01:49:52,634
One hog?

1097
01:49:54,135 --> 01:49:55,887
You sure about that, Johns?

1098
01:50:01,893 --> 01:50:04,437
He pulled the goddamn turbine pin!

1099
01:50:05,939 --> 01:50:07,982
You just figured that out?

1100
01:50:08,566 --> 01:50:12,028
Diaz was gonna take
the nodes for himself and ghost me.

1101
01:50:12,529 --> 01:50:15,198
He was gonna leave you out here alone.

1102
01:50:15,699 --> 01:50:17,200
So what now?

1103
01:50:24,582 --> 01:50:27,002
Now we switch to our ground game.

1104
01:50:28,586 --> 01:50:31,881
Let's see if that lack of spine
runs in the family.

1105
01:50:33,425 --> 01:50:35,176
(CREATURES SNARLING)

1106
01:50:40,557 --> 01:50:42,475
(ROARS)

1107
01:50:47,772 --> 01:50:48,773
(SHRIEKS)

1108
01:50:50,984 --> 01:50:52,235
(GRUNTING)

1109
01:51:23,933 --> 01:51:25,143
Reload!

1110
01:51:29,606 --> 01:51:30,940
(GRUNTS)

1111
01:51:31,483 --> 01:51:33,151
Watch your head.

1112
01:51:37,447 --> 01:51:39,240
(SHRIEKING)

1113
01:51:40,367 --> 01:51:41,368
(COCKS GUN)

1114
01:51:43,536 --> 01:51:44,621
Go!

1115
01:51:52,045 --> 01:51:53,046
(SHRIEKS)

1116
01:52:15,443 --> 01:52:17,112
(GROWLS)

1117
01:52:23,993 --> 01:52:25,537
(GROANING)

1118
01:52:41,177 --> 01:52:42,178
(GRUNTS)

1119
01:52:50,979 --> 01:52:52,355
(GROANING)

1120
01:52:59,320 --> 01:53:00,321
(BEEPS)

1121
01:53:05,035 --> 01:53:06,369
(CREATURES SNARLING)

1122
01:53:26,723 --> 01:53:27,724
(GROANS)

1123
01:53:43,948 --> 01:53:46,284
(GROANING)

1124
01:53:46,701 --> 01:53:47,827
(PINGS)

1125
01:53:47,911 --> 01:53:48,995
I got inbound.

1126
01:54:03,093 --> 01:54:04,094
(GRUNTS)

1127
01:54:04,344 --> 01:54:05,929
Take this!

1128
01:54:06,262 --> 01:54:07,972
Is it just you?

1129
01:54:08,890 --> 01:54:11,226
Just slam this thing in.
See if it's still good. (GRUNTS)

1130
01:54:11,267 --> 01:54:13,353
(GRUNTING)

1131
01:54:14,604 --> 01:54:15,605
Boss...

1132
01:54:15,689 --> 01:54:19,234
Just see if the fucking thing works!
We need to get outta here.

1133
01:54:22,779 --> 01:54:25,281
(GROANING AND PANTING)

1134
01:54:54,686 --> 01:54:55,687
(GROANS IN PAIN)

1135
01:55:02,527 --> 01:55:03,528
(YELLS)

1136
01:55:04,946 --> 01:55:06,281
(GROANING IN PAIN)

1137
01:55:11,286 --> 01:55:12,829
(PANTING)

1138
01:55:54,704 --> 01:55:56,539
(GRUNTING)

1139
01:56:09,969 --> 01:56:11,596
(CREATURES SNARLING)

1140
01:56:17,686 --> 01:56:18,687
(GRUNTING)

1141
01:56:36,579 --> 01:56:37,664
(YELLS)

1142
01:56:41,710 --> 01:56:43,086
(GRUNTING)

1143
01:56:43,712 --> 01:56:45,088
(SCREECHING)

1144
01:56:46,631 --> 01:56:48,091
(GRUNTING)

1145
01:56:59,269 --> 01:57:00,270
(GROWLING)

1146
01:57:19,831 --> 01:57:21,958
(GROWLING)

1147
01:57:24,794 --> 01:57:26,421
(YELLS)

1148
01:57:34,971 --> 01:57:36,765
(YELLING)

1149
01:57:36,806 --> 01:57:38,224
(SNARLING)

1150
01:58:02,874 --> 01:58:04,292
(SILENCE)

1151
01:58:13,843 --> 01:58:15,720
(SPACESHIP APPROACHING)

1152
01:58:23,561 --> 01:58:27,148
Extraction, 30 seconds or less.
Let's go, let's go!

1153
01:58:48,044 --> 01:58:49,045
(ROPE ZINGS)

1154
01:58:59,723 --> 01:59:01,558
Let me ask you somethin',

1155
01:59:02,767 --> 01:59:04,561
sweet-like...

1156
01:59:46,269 --> 01:59:48,104
JOHNS ON RADIO:<i>
Lot of good men died here, Riddick.</i>

1157
01:59:48,521 --> 01:59:52,442
Not sure how I'm supposed
to overlook that. Next time.

1158
01:59:52,817 --> 01:59:54,861
Yeah. Things would have been different

1159
01:59:54,944 --> 01:59:57,280
if they weren't trying
to put my head in a box.

1160
01:59:59,991 --> 02:00:02,035
So where to now, Riddick?

1161
02:00:02,702 --> 02:00:06,623
You know what? Fuck that.
Don't tell me. I don't wanna know.

1162
02:00:07,457 --> 02:00:09,459
<i>I'll tell you this, Johns.</i>

1163
02:00:09,834 --> 02:00:13,046
<i>Sooner or later,
we all have to head home.</i>

1164
02:00:14,047 --> 02:00:16,257
<i>Tell Dahl to keep it warm for me.</i>

1165
02:00:17,050 --> 02:00:18,551
And, Johns,

1166
02:00:19,803 --> 02:00:21,888
you keep a strong spine.

1167
02:00:37,821 --> 02:00:38,822
(MUTTERING)

1168
02:01:09,352 --> 02:01:10,353
RIDDICK: Vaako.

1169
02:01:13,314 --> 02:01:15,734
- You are still alive.
- Tell me where.

1170
02:01:17,902 --> 02:01:19,738
He's no longer among us.

1171
02:01:19,821 --> 02:01:22,824
Tell me, and I'll kill him first.

1172
02:01:23,408 --> 02:01:24,659
You misunderstand.

1173
02:01:25,201 --> 02:01:28,038
Vaako is a decent man
who meant to honor his word.

1174
02:01:28,747 --> 02:01:30,707
Even with you, strangely.

1175
02:01:30,915 --> 02:01:32,584
I don't care about Furya.

1176
02:01:32,667 --> 02:01:35,295
I don't care what the pact
was between you and him.

1177
02:01:35,378 --> 02:01:37,672
This faith cannot have
a misbeliever

1178
02:01:37,714 --> 02:01:39,215
or a kind heart leading it,

1179
02:01:39,257 --> 02:01:42,302
and I have done what
I have done to ensure... (GROANING)

1180
02:01:49,476 --> 02:01:50,602
(THUDDING)

1181
02:01:52,270 --> 02:01:53,855
Too many words.

1182
02:02:08,912 --> 02:02:11,247
Never lie to me,
I'll never hurt you.

1183
02:02:14,918 --> 02:02:16,336
One word answer.

1184
02:02:18,755 --> 02:02:20,256
Is Vaako alive or dead?

1185
02:02:25,762 --> 02:02:26,763
Both.

1186
